snippet.title: Best tech cars
snippet.description: The following cars represent the most technically advanced available.

snippet.title: Belkin WeMo Insight Switch
snippet.description: Despite a few usability quirks, Belkin's WeMo Insight Switch only improves on the simple, low-risk formula that made Belkin's original programmable WeMo Switch so appealing as a home automation starting point.

snippet.title: 2013 Honda Fit EV
snippet.description: The Honda Fit EV shows range similar to that of other compact electric cars on the market and drives well enough, but ultimately feels like a retrofit project car rather than a fully realized futuristic production vehicle.

snippet.title: 2014 Honda Accord Plug-in
snippet.description: The 2014 Honda Accord Plug-in keeps up with the competition in some ways, but the overall package lacks cohesion, and quirky features such as the right-side camera don't add much.

snippet.title: 2010 Honda Insight EX
snippet.description: While the 2010 Honda Insight EX with navigation may not be as mileage-friendly as the Prius, it represents a much better value and is more fun to drive.

snippet.title: 2014 Honda Civic Si Coupe
snippet.description: Unveiled at the 2013 SEMA Show, the refreshed Civic Si Coupe backs up its sharper looks with a small power and performance bump.

snippet.title: 2013 Honda Accord Coupe
snippet.description: The 2013 Honda Accord Coupe EX-L V-6 is a big step in the right direction for Honda, with great performance and good tech, but we worry that all of these virtues may not trickle down to the rest of the brand.

snippet.title: 2012 Honda Civic Hybrid
snippet.description: The 2012 Honda Civic Hybrid's green tech and driver aids boost efficiency without greatly compromising performance or comfort.

snippet.title: Huawei Vision with Ray (Odin Mobile)
snippet.description: The Project Ray operating system can turn a modest Android phone like the Huawei Vision into a device for the seeing-impaired. Get CNET's first impressions of the reenvisioned smartphone here.

snippet.title: 2013 Honda Fit EV
snippet.description: Is the 2013 Honda Fit EV a better ride than a golf cart? CNET's Brian Cooley test drives the all-electric Fit and checks the tech.
